Go to https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/
Select the stable installer file and download the amd64 file 
Open the amd64 file 
Do not forget to select "Add Python to PATH" check button. 

Once the setup is complete:
win + R  and type cmd and hit the enter key 

In the command promt window :
C:\Users\Admin>python
'python' is not recognized as an internal or external command,
operable program or batch file.

If you get the above error, try this. 

C:\Users\Admin>py
Python 3.8.7 (tags/v3.8.7:6503f05, Dec 21 2020, 17:59:51) [MSC v.1928 64 bit (AMD64)] on win32
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
>>>
